  • 【Note】Neutral wire is required in your switch boxes to operate correctly; only supports 2.4 GHz network (Not 5 GHz); offers easy pairing via WiFi and Bluetooth connectivity; Not Dimmer Switch.
  • 【Multi-Control Association】New idea for 3-way circuit (2 switches control 1 light) with multi-control association of this switch to other WiFi smart switches via app; also can be used as single pole circuit; anti-scratch tempered glass panel suits any home decor and allows for effortless touch control; you can multi-control associate this switch to multiple different switches in app.
  • 【Non-interference Control Mode】Allows the switch to be controlled via Smart Life, touch control, voice, and built-in RF433 frequency allows for another control via RF remote control switch with encoding 1527 (remote not included); each control method works independently; achieve multi-control by associating to other smart switches.
  • 【Remote Control】Reinsert new features into upgraded Smart Life Tuya App like ON/OFF relay status as remember last status when power off and backlight switch setting; compatible with Alexa and Google Home for hands-free voice control; can also be controlled via Smart Life/Tuya app anytime, anywhere.
  • 【Customize Schedule and Timer】Take full control of connected appliances with timers, schedules and countdown (1/5/30 mins, 1 hour, etc.) with the app; share control with family and friends for added convenience.

Product description

Moes WiFi Smart Touch Wall Switch

Enjoy your Smart Life with MoesGo Products.

Moes Smart Home device is devoted to household smart products.This new designed glass panel wireless touch smart switch is designed with WiFi+RF to replace traditional switches with a variety of ways to control.Now one new smart feature as multi-control association to other smart switches is added into the Smart Life/Tuya App,together with the backlight on/off and relay status.And its scratch resistance glass panel is suitable for different decoration styles with its best value.

Package Listing

  • Moes WiFi Smart Touch Wall Switch *1
  • Screw*2
  • User Manul*1

Specification

  • Working voltage: 100-240V AC,50/60Hz
  • Current type: Total 10A（pure resistive load）
  • Wireless type: Wi-Fi 2.4GHz
  • Power consumption: ≤0.5W
  • Working temperature: 0℃~40℃
  • RF Frequency: 433MHz
  • RF Standard Code: 1527


Voice control

  • Free hands via easy voice control with Alexa or Google Home


Timer Function

  • Timing setting and countdown options.
  • Control your lights in advance.


Multiple Control

  • You can create group in the APP to manage all the lights in your house and share the device to your family members.


Luxury Glass Panel

  • High quality tempered glass.
  • Water proof.


New ON/OFF Relay Status in App

  • More personalized settings as ON/OFF/Remember last status when power off.


Note

  • Neutral wire is required in your switch boxes to operate correctly
  • Only supports 2.4G network

How to achieve multi-control association in Smart Life App for 3 way feature?

  • Daniel
    5.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
    Took a bit to get it working the way I want.
    Reviewed in the United States on February 19, 2022
    Style: 4 Gang Black (Neutral Wire Required)
    The switches glow at night extremely faintly, you can only see it when standing next to in. This is a nice touch in the bedroom because you can't see the glow from more than a few feet away, but allows you to see them when you are turning things on. I bought... See more
    The switches glow at night extremely faintly, you can only see it when standing next to in. This is a nice touch in the bedroom because you can't see the glow from more than a few feet away, but allows you to see them when you are turning things on.

    I bought this so that I could control smart bulbs in ceiling fixture independently. This made the installation a bit more difficult.

    First I hardwired the light to always be on and bypass the switch. This is needed so that the smart bulbs both have power at all times. I wired the positive and negative from the breaker to the switch. This allows the switch to work, and the lights to be powered.

    Next in the smart life app, I added my bulbs and the switches. Unfortunately alexa does not allow switches in a routine. Instead I had to create scenes in Smart Life.

    When switch one is turned on, turn on bulb one.
    When switch one is turned off, turn off bulb one.
    When bulb one is turned on, turn on switch one.
    When bulb two is turned off, turn off switch one.

    The last two are needed to turn on and off the switch light when I control the light by voice. I then did this for the other bulb as well as my back yard light.

    In Alexa I can then just add the bulbs to allow me to control color and I can turn them off which will trigger the switch to turn off as well. I can also then setup routines in alexa that will turn the lights off after 30 minutes if I wanted to, and the switch will work as expected.

Con neutro por otro lado, no requiere el capacitor pero sí un cable. Tuvo problemas de intermitencia en un principio y después de unos minutos se apagaban. Me ha sucedido unas 4 o 5 veces al principio, pero ahora ya no ha presentado el problema, es probable que se trate de un tema de mi WiFi. Mes mucho más barato y sencillo que cualquier otro de marca conocida, además no requiere controlador, por lo que es 4 veces más barato. Lo recomiendo.
